      <p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong style=
      "font-size: 14px;">1.&nbsp; Attend the Earn A Bike Orientation
      Class</strong></span></p>

      <p><span style="font-size:14px;">Our E</span>arn A Bike Orientation
      class is an interactive hands-on experience where participants
      learn the basics of bicycle safety, maintenance, and bicycle theft
      prevention. Topics covered include: how to ride a bicycle in
      traffic safetly, proper helmet usage, fixing a flat, maintaining
      your bicycle, checking for worn/broken parts, performing a safety
      check on your bicycle, and bicycle theft prevention. These classes
      are held on Saturday afternoons and advanced registration is highly
      recommended.</p>

      <p>&nbsp;</p>

      <p><img alt="" src=
      "/images/Photos/382479_10150930813641150_506306074_n.jpg" style=
      "height: 207px; width: 160px; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; float: left;"></p>

      <p><span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>2. &nbsp;Give Your
      Time</strong></span></p>

      <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size:12px;">Once
      you've attended the EAB Orientation Class, you will be asked to
      complete 3 hours of community service. You may volunteer yout time
      at the Bike Depot, choose another organization we have
      pre-approved, or choose an organization of your choice*.</span></p>

      <p>&nbsp;</p>

      <p><img alt="" src=
      "/images/Photos/547233_10150852465066150_1203202546_n.jpg" style=
      "height: 188px; width: 250px; float: right; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;"></p>

      <p>&nbsp;</p>

      <p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong style=
      "font-size: 14px;">3. &nbsp;Build Your Bike</strong></span></p>

      <p>The third and final step of the program is to come to the Bike
      Depot, pick out your bike, and spend about 3 hours working on it
      with the help of a BD volunteer. Upon successful completion of the
      program, you will also receive a helmet, lock, and headlight.
      <strong>Build A Bike appointments are only available at the
      following times:</strong> Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays 1pm-4pm,
      Thursdays 4pm-7pm, and Fridays 11am-2pm and 2pm-5pm. These times
      are not flexible, so please consult your schedule when considering
      whether or not to do the program.</p>

      <p>&nbsp;</p>

      <p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>

      <p style="text-align: center;">If you're ready to sign up to
      participate in the program, the first step is to schedule your
      Orientation Class. These do fill up as space is limited. You may
      call the shop during open hours or stop by.</p>

      <p style="text-align: center;">By phone, please call us at
      303-393-1963 and select extension 2. Please be ready to leave a
      message with your name, number, address and someone will get back
      to you in a timely manner to schedule your Orientation.</p>

      <p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>

      <p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>

      <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:16px;">To
      date,&nbsp;<strong>1,462 bicycles</strong> have been earned through
      our Earn A Bike program!&nbsp;</span></p>

      <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:16px;">Call
      or stop by the Bike Depot to register or if you have any questions
      about the program.</span></p>
